{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In a study conducted by Zhou et al. (2022), transcriptome profiling of maize genotypes exposed to heat or cold stress revealed extensive alterations in transcript abundance.",
    "Motifs near the transcription start sites (TSSs) of genes responsive to thermal stress were found to be enriched.",
    "Predictive models developed using these motifs could forecast gene expression responses to stress, with enhanced accuracy focusing on motifs within unmethylated regions near the TSSs.",
    "However, challenges emerged when applying these models across different maize genotypes, indicating reduced performance when transferred between genotypes.",
    "In a recent study, Pradhan et al. (2023a) employed artificial intelligence, specifically ML, to tackle the challenge of identifying long non-coding RNAs (lncRNAs) associated with abiotic stress responses in plants."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In a study conducted by Zhou et al. (2022), transcriptome profiling of maize genotypes exposed to heat or cold stress revealed extensive alterations in transcript abundance.",
